AMAXHOSA King Zwelonke Sigcawu is happy the screening of the film Inxeba: The Wound has been suspended in cinemas in the Eastern Cape and in parts of Cape Town.The king watched the film during a special screening in Joburg last year and said it was a disgrace to the Xhosa culture.Speaking to the SunTeam from his royal Nqadu Place in Willowvale, the king said the film should not have made it into cinemas to begin with.Chief Mkhanyiseli Dudumayo, provincial secretary of the Congress of Traditional Leaders, said a meeting will be organised with cinemas, producers and traditional leaders until an agreement is reached.ALSO READ: LOYISO COMES UNDER ATTACK!if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjsuuDbu5oa-yUnhyALmHxQ21SkPvlqKE3cXk-zViQ1CnjmLhg3Xs3CGYnfL0aFR_DJ5HSlAOxuH2zKiCwDZ0FBNFzONL-gNEYf9cOvcQnHkDNQpWALQsmpH1GWW_I-IBj0bZr7mBczKNQAl03LmkyocL-zezZzBdFmTHoZancS_fGqJhf2mHck2J0GnZXaAH1RmB5GsYXOM9_y-DOJq1o8561uKqO9JORMcyw4DHpKWJHTvbb91WFPAN8szdlL2TJLQVqCAcxqcJfqthREH7iGx_Vuu3ZthjHpHQ0g\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzB-ThelVLGudEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
